733253f-a.title: Squatters Colony at the Hudson River [Dyckman Camp.]
733253f-a.folder: Dyckman Street and Staff Avenue, Manhattan, N.Y.

719397f-a.text:
Dyckman Street, west from Staff Street (seen in foreground) to the North (Hudson) River. Shown spanning this thoroughfare are the Henry Hudson Parkway structure and the New York Central Railroad bed. The first mentioned has just been completed and is a portion of the West Side Improvement Project which was opened to the public on October 12,
1937.
April 14, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
